1.What is a port and why do we need them?
A port is a logical communication endpoint used by a computer to identify a specific service or application on a network.
We need ports because a computer can run many services at the same time(web browsing,email,file,transfer etc.) and ports help send data to the correct application.
2.What is the difference well known ports,registered ports and dynamic ports?
well known ports(0-1023) are reserved for common services and protocols.
resgistered [orts(1024-49151) are used by specific applications and organizations.
dynamic ports(49152-65535) are temporarily used or assigned for client-side communication.
3.Name 5 important port numbers and what they are used for?
Port 80-HTTP-used for web pages(non secure browsing).
Port 443-HTTPS-used for secure web browsing.
Port 21-FTP-used for file transfer.
Port 25-SMTP-used for sending emails.
Port 53-DNS-used for domain name resolution.
